INFLAMMATORY BREAST CANCER has a clinical presentation of BREAST SWELLING erythema, warmth, and a peau d'orange appearance (characterized by a dimpled appearance caused by tumor infiltration of intradermal lymphatics); it may or may not be associated with a mass. These lesions are associated with a high risk of recurrence of local disease and with distant metastases.
